<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" ID="Table5">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" ID="Table6">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=2465">Mistmoore Castle</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Blade of Malevolence</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Blade of Malevolence</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=464413"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:sacutis@aol.com">One of Three</a> | 
		                        7/9/2001 2:26:48 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">I do find the most interesting things in my travels, but this by far was the most horrific I've ever come across. No one word could best describe what was going through my mind when it happened but, I'll try and give you an explination....<BR>
<BR>
Not long ago, I was fooling around on the roof of the Mistmoor castle. I wasn't killing MoBs, just observing them. I saw a strange spell coming out of one of the tower corners, it looked... Different. I went to investigate and then I heard the words &quot;My faithful follower, what have they done to you?&quot;. Afterwards there was a bit of ruckus and I saw a high level trying to get out of the tower through the wall. I targeted him and /assisted. For what it's wourth, I give sympathy the following is hard to believe, but this is something that I really feel is worth hearing.<BR>
<BR>
I acquired the target of Mayong Mistmoor. He was obviously in a less than pleasant mood. The high level that was trying to escape, I forget his name, perished relatively quickly. Mayong went on to summon a necromancer pet and I slinked over to the wall. I conned him indifferently and figured it was a bug but as it turns out, he's on the wierdest faction you can possibly imagine. If you're KOS to all pre-kunark/velious cities, he doesn't KOS you, or so is my theory (also KOS to Antonica Bards).<BR>
<BR>
Any way, I snuck around a bit and using levitate I tricked my way down on to a ledge against the wall. I figured I had 5 minutes to chat with him and believe me, screen shots were the last thing on my mind (my Compaq computer is bugged, when I take an SS my screen locks up for about 6 minutes).<BR>
<BR>
I got to work and asked him: &quot;What Ring of the Scale&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'Cursed Dragons, why won't they leave me be?! As I look back now, I feel like I may have made a mistake but if they would only understand the risk letting it free would be!'<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'Who is he?'<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'Who are they?'<BR>
<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'The Ring of the Scale punish me to no end for saving their pathedic lives! On the dawn of creation, Veeshan sent her first born to us who would one day destroy all existence if for any reason should the dragons loose control. I discovered this by speaking with Lord Nagafen when he was but a hatchling with a big mouth.'<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'Who is Veeshan's first born?'<BR>
<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'His name was Kerafyrm. This was a dragon like no other. The mere word in his day would kill a man with fear. When I sought him to plead for the indepidence of my kind from the Dragons, I to learned fear. A voice that rocked the lands, a body like a mountain, all the Gods together would weep in terror in his shadow. However, he was not without a weakness...'<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'If this is a GM, I'm sooo gonna kill you'<BR>
<BR>
You say, '....'<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'What weakness?'<BR>
<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'When I met with Kerafyrm for the first time, I knew right then and there that I could never even dream of killing such a creation. But I had to find a way to delay him until I could. Kerafyrm is a very playful and lowly creator, despite his glory and mighty existence. I managed to convince four of the strongest magic wielders alive that he was plotting to destroy all existence in the name of the Ring of the Scale.'<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'What became of Kerafyrm?'<BR>
<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'I swore my soul to my King that I would achieve our freedom from the Dragons and it cost me just that. In order to battle the mighty Kerafyrm long enough for the four whom followed me to force him asleep, I contested my soul for immortality. I cannot describe the agony it was to loose my soul and if I had a second chance to make that choice, I would debate it. In my hand I hold a fragment of the blade I used to wage a war on Kerafyrm that lasted six years.'<BR>
<BR>
Auto-Attack is on.<BR>
You can't hit them from here!<BR>
You can't hit them from here!<BR>
Auto-Attack is off.<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'What blade?'<BR>
<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'The Blade of Malevolence, created by Innoruuk and Cazic-Thule with my eternal soul and their physical bodies. A living blade with my soul and their flesh, it would carve through a mountain of velium as quickly as a man could blink. As I fought against Kerafyrm, the blade slowly wore against his scales. At the end of the battle just before he was sealed off, he used all of his remaining energy to see to it that I only had this chance once, and that should I fail and he ever wake again, the world would know it was my fault that they were going to die.'<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'What happened to The Blade of Malevolence?'<BR>
<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'It was frozen, burned, shattered, crushed and melted then cast across all of Norrath. Using the fraction of my Soul, The Kraken had crafted The Godslayer. Using the fraction of Innoruuk's body, men had crafted A Glowing Black Stone. Using the fraction of Cazic-Thule's body, men have crafted Pademonium. The hilt was destroyed. To replace it I would need a Jagged Shard of Velium Ice and The Teeth of three tainted dragons. If only I still had a soul I could venture forth and reclaim these items with ease...'<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'I will reclaim them for you'<BR>
<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'This is only a fraction of a much larger story. On your ventures, remember, even the mightiest weapons, armor and magic are bits and pieces of something you could never even imagine. If you assist me on this task, I will do two things for you; I will tell you the location of Omega and I will give you The Blade of Malevolence.'<BR>
<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'Fools who have disturbed my rest! I shall tear the flesh from your bones!'<BR>
Mayong Mistmoor says, 'Filfthy gnomes like you must die!'<BR>
<BR>
About three seconds later a few curious people were dead and Mayong proply depoped. It looks like I've stumbled on to something relatively big here... Perhaps there is a plot to this game?<BR>
<BR>
If I get a chance to complete this quest (though I'm not counting on it), you'll be the first to hear. Should you attempt this quest, remember the risks.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
