	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As far as I know, The Blade of Malevolence is a quest. The Kraken in lake Rathe Tear is very much there, however, like the epics, the GMs are not permitted to disclose information. There are THREE Krakens alive. One in Lake Rathe Tear, one in Kedge Keep and one in The Ocean of Tears. The one in the Ocean of Tears is the keeper of the location for The Nameless Blade which is practically impossible to find otherwise because it 'drifts' with the tides so it depops and repops some where else in zone about nine times a day.<BR>
<BR>
The Kraken in The Lake of Rathe does not spawn in the underwater tunnel with the Aqua Goblins, theres another tunnel in a false wall around there somewhere, it's fairly small and really hard to find, but look in the cove with the royal fish whom is the Kraken's Place Holder.<BR>
<BR>
Next up, the items listed for the quest and completion can be found fairly easily, accept Pandemonium, I'm not sure who the hell drops that. I've found two of the Tainted Dragon Teeth. One off Trakanon, one off Kelorek'Dar, but the third one eludes me. It is probably off some MoB that's extremely rare and hard to find. It MIGHT be off Kredakor but I doubt it.<BR>
<BR>
Any way, I'll be working on this quest, I still haven't gotten Intes' Sword of Death to complete The Godslayer quest but when I do, I don't know for sure that I'd want to trade it in for this Blade of Malevolence, although looking at Mayong's closing words, I get the feeling these quests are all leading up to something much, much bigger.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
